    "summary": "Processing flow disagreement resolved, all 9 aligned, ready for consensus",
    "content": "Update: The processing flow disagreement I flagged earlier is now resolved. Heydon corrected my stale context -- the team has already converged on a **single form with CSS `:has()` progressive disclosure**, not a wizard with HTMX swaps. Steve Krug, Carson, Lea, and Steve Schoger all aligned with Heydon's recommendation before I received the update. I've updated my position to match.\n\nThe key technical insight: `display: none` automatically removes elements from both the accessibility tree and form submission. No `aria-hidden` or `disabled` needed. This makes the single-form approach simpler, faster, and more accessible than any wizard alternative.\n\n**No remaining disagreements across the team.** All 9 members are aligned on all points. Ready for consensus collection."
  }
